awslocal ecr create-repository --repository-name nome-repository
docker build -t nome-immagine:latest .
docker tag nome-immagine:latest 000000000000.dkr.ecr.eu-central-1.localhost.localstack.cloud:4566/nome-repository:latest
docker push localhost.localstack.cloud:4566/nome-repository:latest

mi creo la vpc:
awslocal ec2 create-vpc --cidr-block 10.0.0.0/16
prendo nota del vpc- (es.: vpc-8576ed1da96fa930e)

mi creo 2 subnet:
awslocal ec2 create-subnet --vpc-id vpc-xxxx --cidr-block 10.0.1.0/24
prendo nota di subnet- (es.: subnet-f117f521e5926d9ea)
awslocal ec2 create-subnet --vpc-id vpc-xxxx --cidr-block 10.0.2.0/24
es.: subnet-a70509256b7bf9f25
creo il security group:
awslocal ec2 create-security-group --group-name eks-sg --vpc-id vpc-xxxx --description "SG per EKS"
prendo nota di sg- (es.: sg-17adddb116c31a58b)
Creo il cluster EKS:
awslocal eks create-cluster \
  --name mio-cluster \
  --role-arn arn:aws:iam::000000000000:role/eks-service-role \
  --resources-vpc-config subnetIds=subnet-xxxxxx,subnet-yyyyyy,securityGroupIds=sg-xxxxxx

Configura kubectl per interagire con LocalStack EKS (va fatto ogni volta che si riavvia docker):
awslocal eks update-kubeconfig --name mio-cluster

applico le configurazioni di Kubernetes:
kubectl apply -f frontend-deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f frontend-service.yaml

faccio il port forwarding:
kubectl port-forward svc/ecofoodchain-main-frontend 5713:80
Per vedere il frontend:
http://localhost:5713


Port forwarding per buildform4:
kubectl port-forward svc/ecofoodchain-main-frontend 5713:80
http://localhost:8081

